steps.description:
The materials you use depend on what kind of clown you want to be. However, there are some general props that are used by many clowns, such as balls for juggling, balloons for making balloon animals, magic trick props if you're doing tricks, and any other silly props you can think of. You can start off with the traditional tools and become more original as you discover who your inner clown really is. Get your music together if it's part of your act. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/23/Be-a-Clown-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Be-a-Clown-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/23/Be-a-Clown-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Be-a-Clown-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Part of your act may include putting face paint on children. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e3/Be-a-Clown-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Be-a-Clown-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e3/Be-a-Clown-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Be-a-Clown-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If ventriloquism is part of your act, then get yourself a dummy. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/63/Be-a-Clown-Step-1Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Be-a-Clown-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/63/Be-a-Clown-Step-1Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Be-a-Clown-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Contrary to popular belief, not all clowns wear face paint. Clowning is a style of comedy, not a style of makeup. Most clowns use greasepaint for their faces, since this kind doesn't wash off as easily as water-based paint or Halloween paint. If you do put on makeup, there are a variety of makeup styles you can try:
Whiteface clown paint. This is the traditional face paint that you may think of when you want to look like a clown. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/fc/Be-a-Clown-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Be-a-Clown-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/fc/Be-a-Clown-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Be-a-Clown-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Auguste clown paint. This type of clown wears makeup that is a bit more flesh-toned. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/54/Be-a-Clown-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Be-a-Clown-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/54/Be-a-Clown-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Be-a-Clown-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Tramp or hobo clown paint. This face paint is a bit darker and sooty looking, because this type of clown is down on his luck. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d3/Be-a-Clown-Step-3Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Be-a-Clown-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d3/Be-a-Clown-Step-3Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Be-a-Clown-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Character clown paint. What kind of clown do you want to be? Mad scientist? Keystone cop clown? Your character will determine the color and style of makeup you use. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/97/Be-a-Clown-Step-3Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Be-a-Clown-Step-3Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/97/Be-a-Clown-Step-3Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Be-a-Clown-Step-3Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Get an idea for major comedy points you want to include, and work out the lead-up and other parts of the comedy. Thinking about problems that need addressing can be a good start e.g a hat that won't stay on your head , or a music stand that keeps falling over. A twist at the end may help, as can thinking about the rule of three (e.g mistake, mistake, success) in an unexpected way. It's almost like a play. If you're so minded, script your act before rehearsal! Here are some things clowns often include in their shows:
Making balloon animals{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9f/Be-a-Clown-Step-5Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Be-a-Clown-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9f/Be-a-Clown-Step-5Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Be-a-Clown-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Miming{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/79/Be-a-Clown-Step-5Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Be-a-Clown-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/79/Be-a-Clown-Step-5Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Be-a-Clown-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Juggling{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/90/Be-a-Clown-Step-5Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Be-a-Clown-Step-5Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/90/Be-a-Clown-Step-5Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Be-a-Clown-Step-5Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Storytelling{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/62/Be-a-Clown-Step-5Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Be-a-Clown-Step-5Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/62/Be-a-Clown-Step-5Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Be-a-Clown-Step-5Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Ventriloquism{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e2/Be-a-Clown-Step-5Bullet5.jpg/v4-460px-Be-a-Clown-Step-5Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e2/Be-a-Clown-Step-5Bullet5.jpg/v4-760px-Be-a-Clown-Step-5Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Jokes{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4f/Be-a-Clown-Step-5Bullet6.jpg/v4-460px-Be-a-Clown-Step-5Bullet6.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4f/Be-a-Clown-Step-5Bullet6.jpg/v4-760px-Be-a-Clown-Step-5Bullet6.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

There is nothing a clown has to do. Unless you have a twist on the obvious, you should try to avoid the most obvious clowning tricks if you want to be successful. Here are some moves that you should generally stay away from:
Slipping on banana skins{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/86/Be-a-Clown-Step-8Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Be-a-Clown-Step-8Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/86/Be-a-Clown-Step-8Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Be-a-Clown-Step-8Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Falling over{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9e/Be-a-Clown-Step-8Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Be-a-Clown-Step-8Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9e/Be-a-Clown-Step-8Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Be-a-Clown-Step-8Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Chasing your sidekick around{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/8e/Be-a-Clown-Step-8Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Be-a-Clown-Step-8Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/8e/Be-a-Clown-Step-8Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Be-a-Clown-Step-8Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Getting soaked in buckets of water{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/89/Be-a-Clown-Step-8Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Be-a-Clown-Step-8Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/89/Be-a-Clown-Step-8Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Be-a-Clown-Step-8Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

